column8: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Sensors -  If the ship goes dark, don't panic. Just fix the Sensors Subsystem.
Thank you. Here, have this extra scrap as payment.

It's unlikely the Rock's impressive immune system is susceptible to a human virus so you send it in. It is able to intimidate the workers long enough for the colony forces to set up a quarantine. Their leaders offer a reward and assure you they will try to find a cure as soon as possible.
With most of the fire under control, the scientists are able to help secure the station. They offer you their sincere gratitude and a generous reward.
The clone is extremely confused but calms down after you try to explain the situation. With no other options the clone offers to work on your ship for a time.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Your scans reveal a mining base on a nearby planet long since abandoned. No life signs detected.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.
With the pirate ship destroyed, your ship's system is restored to full functionality. You salvage what you can from the debris.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You arrive in the nebula and immediately receive a message from an unknown source, Prepare to be boarded! With the static from the nebula, there's no way to tell where they came from, but you hear shots fired on board the ship.

You find two heavily damaged ships floating nearby, the remains of a battle. You begin to harvest some usable debris when you hear the sounds of someone beaming aboard followed by the shouts of a boarding party.
With the crew dead, you search the ship. You find military-grade weaponry and take what looks most useful.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
This sector was hit hard by the rebellion. The many alien settlements and stations located here are now watched over by almost an equal number of Rebel bases, heavy-handedly 'keeping the peace'.
There is a small planet nearby with scattered settlements. A small Rebel fleet is in orbit with many ships ferrying back and forth. It must be a more recently 'liberated' planet.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You discover a re-supply station used by Rebels and civilians alike. You transmit your fake ship identification and for once, they don't seem to recognize your ship. You try to assume the air of a local as you prepare to dock.

column8: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You power up your weapons and engage the Rebel ship.
You successfully hack into their system and transmit false information about your location. That should hold off the fleet for at least a little while.
This sector has become increasingly dangerous for friends of the Federation. I think my crew can patch up some of your hull damage as thanks.
You arrive in an asteroid belt to discover that a Rebel automated-scout has been stationed here. Prepare for a fight!

You find the planet at the indicated coordinates. Your initial scans show the planet to be barren and devoid of life, but you get a prompt reply when you broadcast on Federation frequencies. Hello! So nice to see friends. We'll bring you up some supplies.
At least you're confident, for what little that's worth. Here is their last known location. Added a quest marker to the next sector!
You arrive at a small space station that is putting out wide-band broadcasts on black-market channels. You doubt they would turn away any business, regardless of allegiances.

column8: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You've entered a poorly charted area of space that's known to be home to the Mantis. Ensure your hull plating is up to scratch and that you have enough fuel in the tank to make it through.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
KazaaakplethKilik fights to the last, and you pick the scraps from the corpse of his ship. You sense, though, that his death has left a great mystery unresolved.

A nearby Mantis mining operation is clearly using heavy Engi slave labor. You briefly consider the possibility of emancipating the slaves, but the Mantis presence is too formidable. You decide to lay low.
You accidentally reactivate the ship's AI. Its weapons immediately go online; prepare for a fight!

You fire a few volleys from a distance and it is clear the defense system is no match for your weapons. However, the station does not seem happy with your 'solution'. You salvage what you can and jump before there is trouble.
You receive a transmission: Sorry sir, this is nothing personal but we're under orders. The Rebel ship's weapons go hot.
At this point you almost expect a fight with the Mantis, but this beacon appears to be entirely devoid of other ships. You take the time to catch your breath and double check the ship's systems.
A Mantis military ship appears on local radar alongside the remains of a human freighter. Prepare for a hostile encounter!

The Rebels are already here! The crew braces for impact, but none comes. The sensors report the unmanned rebel supply ship is malfunctioning and is stuck in vending mode - for a little scrap you can take your pick.
column9: System: medbay, mind, hacking, Augment: ION ARMOR, REPAIR ARM, EXPLOSIVE REPLICATOR, Weapon: LASER BURST 5, BOMB 1, LASER BURST 3, Drone: DEFENSE 1, SHIP REPAIR, ANTI DRONE,

column8: You find the station that had ordered your cargo. You drop it off and they respond, Ignoring the fact that this is days late, we really appreciate that you delivered our materials. We realize how dangerous this sector is these days. Take this as payment.
The Mantis is shocked to see the crewmember it just slaughtered step out of the Clone Bay.

It's unlikely the Rock's impressive immune system is susceptible to a human virus so you send it in. It is able to intimidate the workers long enough for the colony forces to set up a quarantine. Their leaders offer a reward and assure you they will try to find a cure as soon as possible.
The only thing this beacon offers is a view of deep space and a brief respite from battles. For some this must be a welcome refuge.

Merchants are not highly respected among the Mantis race, so few undertake the profession. You're mildly surprised to receive an advertisement from a nearby space dock. You decide to see what they have to offer.

column8: Their ship breaks apart and you move in to scrap the remains.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
All around you is the stench of death and decay. The life sign readings must have been malfunctioning because you really doubt anything could be alive in here. You quickly return to the ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
This nebula must have been an important hub at one point; placing all of these jump beacons would be no easy task. However, now it's hardly navigable.
The station is a storage site for military grade weapons. You find one that can be easily attached to the ship.
